<subSubSection id="B6BB655F3C08EF06FF40FAF3FB69F814" pageId="1" pageNumber="271" type="description">
<paragraph id="FE1E36D43C08EF06FF40FAF3FEFEFAA8" blockId="1.[151,706,1291,1354]" box="[151,274,1328,1354]" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">
(
<figureCitation id="669A2A513C08EF06FF48FAF3FEE5FAA8" box="[159,265,1328,1354]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2" captionStart-2="FIGURE 3" captionStartId-0="2.[151,250,761,785]" captionStartId-1="2.[151,250,1426,1450]" captionStartId-2="3.[151,250,974,998]" captionTargetBox-0="[164,1422,179,735]" captionTargetBox-1="[165,1422,847,1402]" captionTargetBox-2="[196,1389,387,947]" captionTargetId-0="figure-19@2.[164,1423,179,736]" captionTargetId-1="figure-49@2.[164,1423,846,1403]" captionTargetId-2="figure-134@3.[189,1399,381,951]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="2" captionTargetPageId-2="3" captionText-0="FIGURE 1. Rhopalopsole singiplatta, sp. nov. A. male head and pronotum, dorsal view; B. female head and pronotum, dorsal view; C. female abdominal terminalia, ventral view." captionText-1="FIGURE 2. Rhopalopsole singiplatta, sp. nov. A. male abdominal terminalia, dorsal view; B. male abdominal terminalia, lateral view; C. male abdominal terminalia, ventral view" captionText-2="FIGURE 3. Rhopalopsole singiplatta, sp. nov. A: male abdominal terminalia, dorsal view; B: male abdominal terminalia, ventral view; C: lateral processes of tergum 10." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524476" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524478" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524481" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6524476/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6524478/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6524481/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">Figs. 1–3</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FE1E36D43C08EF06FF40FABBFE00FA1C" blockId="1.[151,1437,1400,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C08EF06FF40FABBFF37FA70" bold="true" box="[151,219,1400,1426]" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">Male.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity id="39599B313C08EF06FEA1FABBFE25FA71" box="[374,457,1400,1427]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
, forewing length 
<quantity id="39599B313C08EF06FD46FABBFD0FFA71" box="[657,739,1400,1427]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
, hindwing length 
<quantity id="39599B313C08EF06FC66FABBFC1FFA71" box="[945,1011,1400,1427]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
(n=1). Head brown, somewhat wider than pronotum (
<figureCitation id="669A2A513C08EF06FE87FA5FFE47FA54" box="[336,427,1436,1462]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,761,785]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,179,735]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[164,1423,179,736]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhopalopsole singiplatta, sp. nov. A. male head and pronotum, dorsal view; B. female head and pronotum, dorsal view; C. female abdominal terminalia, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524476" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524476/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
); ocelli white; antennae and palpi brown. Pronotum brown, quadrate, longer than wide, anterior and posterior corners rounded and with several black irregular stripes (
<figureCitation id="669A2A513C08EF06FBC1FA03FB83FA38" box="[1046,1135,1472,1498]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,761,785]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,179,735]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[164,1423,179,736]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhopalopsole singiplatta, sp. nov. A. male head and pronotum, dorsal view; B. female head and pronotum, dorsal view; C. female abdominal terminalia, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524476" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524476/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Legs light brown. Wings hyaline and veins light brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FE1E36D43C08EF06FF10F9CAFEF8F8A0" blockId="1.[151,1437,1400,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">
Tergum 9 mostly sclerotized, lesser so medially and without ornamentation (
<figureCitation id="669A2A513C08EF06FBF0F9CBFB50F9C0" box="[1063,1212,1544,1570]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1426,1450]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,847,1402]" captionTargetId="figure-49@2.[164,1423,846,1403]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rhopalopsole singiplatta, sp. nov. A. male abdominal terminalia, dorsal view; B. male abdominal terminalia, lateral view; C. male abdominal terminalia, ventral view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524478/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">Figs. 2A, 2B</figureCitation>
). Sternum 9 basally with flabelliform vesicle bearing dense hairs, apically with a triangular subgenital plate (
<figureCitation id="669A2A513C08EF06FBABF9EFFB32F9A4" box="[1148,1246,1580,1606]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1426,1450]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,847,1402]" captionTargetId="figure-49@2.[164,1423,846,1403]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rhopalopsole singiplatta, sp. nov. A. male abdominal terminalia, dorsal view; B. male abdominal terminalia, lateral view; C. male abdominal terminalia, ventral view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524478/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">Figs. 2C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="669A2A513C08EF06FB3CF9EFFAE2F9A4" box="[1259,1294,1580,1606]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,974,998]" captionTargetBox="[196,1389,387,947]" captionTargetId="figure-134@3.[189,1399,381,951]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Rhopalopsole singiplatta, sp. nov. A: male abdominal terminalia, dorsal view; B: male abdominal terminalia, ventral view; C: lateral processes of tergum 10." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524481/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">3B</figureCitation>
). Tergum 10 bearing a central plate covered with macrotrichia with no roughage of cuticular surface at distal end, lateral bars heavily sclerotized (
<figureCitation id="669A2A513C08EF06FEAAF9B7FE0EF96C" box="[381,482,1652,1678]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1426,1450]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,847,1402]" captionTargetId="figure-49@2.[164,1423,846,1403]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rhopalopsole singiplatta, sp. nov. A. male abdominal terminalia, dorsal view; B. male abdominal terminalia, lateral view; C. male abdominal terminalia, ventral view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524478/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">Figs. 2A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="669A2A513C08EF06FE27F9B7FDF9F96C" box="[496,533,1652,1678]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,974,998]" captionTargetBox="[196,1389,387,947]" captionTargetId="figure-134@3.[189,1399,381,951]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Rhopalopsole singiplatta, sp. nov. A: male abdominal terminalia, dorsal view; B: male abdominal terminalia, ventral view; C: lateral processes of tergum 10." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524481/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">3A</figureCitation>
). Lateral projections of tergum 10 originating as a rounded base and extending upwards and backwards in a short plate, ending in a forked process, the lower point slightly smaller (
<figureCitation id="669A2A513C08EF06FAD2F95BFA74F950" box="[1285,1432,1688,1714]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1426,1450]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,847,1402]" captionTargetId="figure-49@2.[164,1423,846,1403]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rhopalopsole singiplatta, sp. nov. A. male abdominal terminalia, dorsal view; B. male abdominal terminalia, lateral view; C. male abdominal terminalia, ventral view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524478/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">Figs. 2A, 2B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="669A2A513C08EF06FF40F97FFF06F934" box="[151,234,1724,1750]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,974,998]" captionTargetBox="[196,1389,387,947]" captionTargetId="figure-134@3.[189,1399,381,951]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Rhopalopsole singiplatta, sp. nov. A: male abdominal terminalia, dorsal view; B: male abdominal terminalia, ventral view; C: lateral processes of tergum 10." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524481/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">3A, 3C</figureCitation>
). Transverse plates roughly triangular (
<figureCitation id="669A2A513C08EF06FD4BF97FFD13F934" box="[668,767,1724,1750]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1426,1450]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,847,1402]" captionTargetId="figure-49@2.[164,1423,846,1403]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rhopalopsole singiplatta, sp. nov. A. male abdominal terminalia, dorsal view; B. male abdominal terminalia, lateral view; C. male abdominal terminalia, ventral view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524478/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">Figs. 2A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="669A2A513C08EF06FCDDF97FFCC3F934" box="[778,815,1724,1750]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,974,998]" captionTargetBox="[196,1389,387,947]" captionTargetId="figure-134@3.[189,1399,381,951]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Rhopalopsole singiplatta, sp. nov. A: male abdominal terminalia, dorsal view; B: male abdominal terminalia, ventral view; C: lateral processes of tergum 10." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524481/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">3A</figureCitation>
). Epiproct thick at base, hook-like, tapering appreciably along its course, ending in a round point (
<figureCitation id="669A2A513C08EF06FDA9F923FCFAF918" box="[638,790,1760,1786]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1426,1450]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,847,1402]" captionTargetId="figure-49@2.[164,1423,846,1403]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rhopalopsole singiplatta, sp. nov. A. male abdominal terminalia, dorsal view; B. male abdominal terminalia, lateral view; C. male abdominal terminalia, ventral view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524478/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">Figs. 2A, 2B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="669A2A513C08EF06FCF3F923FCA5F918" box="[804,841,1760,1786]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,974,998]" captionTargetBox="[196,1389,387,947]" captionTargetId="figure-134@3.[189,1399,381,951]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Rhopalopsole singiplatta, sp. nov. A: male abdominal terminalia, dorsal view; B: male abdominal terminalia, ventral view; C: lateral processes of tergum 10." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524481/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">3A</figureCitation>
). Subanal lobes of medium size, flat and plate-like, expanding posteriorly, with well-defined ventral furrows (
<figureCitation id="669A2A513C08EF06FCCBF8C7FC92F8FC" box="[796,894,1796,1822]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1426,1450]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,847,1402]" captionTargetId="figure-49@2.[164,1423,846,1403]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rhopalopsole singiplatta, sp. nov. A. male abdominal terminalia, dorsal view; B. male abdominal terminalia, lateral view; C. male abdominal terminalia, ventral view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524478/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">Figs. 2C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="669A2A513C08EF06FC5EF8C7FC40F8FC" box="[905,940,1796,1822]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,974,998]" captionTargetBox="[196,1389,387,947]" captionTargetId="figure-134@3.[189,1399,381,951]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Rhopalopsole singiplatta, sp. nov. A: male abdominal terminalia, dorsal view; B: male abdominal terminalia, ventral view; C: lateral processes of tergum 10." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524481/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">3B</figureCitation>
). Cercus hairy and upcurved, no spine (
<figureCitation id="669A2A513C08EF06FAB3F8C7FF4BF8A0" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1426,1450]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,847,1402]" captionTargetId="figure-49@2.[164,1423,846,1403]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rhopalopsole singiplatta, sp. nov. A. male abdominal terminalia, dorsal view; B. male abdominal terminalia, lateral view; C. male abdominal terminalia, ventral view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524478" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524478/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="669A2A513C08EF06FF64F8EBFEEBF8A0" box="[179,263,1832,1858]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,974,998]" captionTargetBox="[196,1389,387,947]" captionTargetId="figure-134@3.[189,1399,381,951]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Rhopalopsole singiplatta, sp. nov. A: male abdominal terminalia, dorsal view; B: male abdominal terminalia, ventral view; C: lateral processes of tergum 10." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524481/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">3A, 3B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FE1E36D43C08EF06FF10F88FFB69F814" blockId="1.[151,1437,1400,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C08EF06FF10F88FFEC9F884" bold="true" box="[199,293,1868,1894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">Female.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity id="39599B313C08EF06FE6CF88FFE11F885" box="[443,509,1868,1895]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
, forewing length 
<quantity id="39599B313C08EF06FD17F88FFCEFF885" box="[704,771,1868,1895]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
, hindwing length 
<quantity id="39599B313C08EF06FC1DF88FFBE6F885" box="[970,1034,1868,1895]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
(n=1). Head dark brown, somewhat wider than pronotum (
<figureCitation id="669A2A513C08EF06FE5CF8B3FE0CF868" box="[395,480,1904,1930]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,761,785]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,179,735]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[164,1423,179,736]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhopalopsole singiplatta, sp. nov. A. male head and pronotum, dorsal view; B. female head and pronotum, dorsal view; C. female abdominal terminalia, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524476" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524476/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
); ocelli white; antennae and palpi brown. Pronotum brown, quadrate, longer than wide, with several black irregular stripes (
<figureCitation id="669A2A513C08EF06FDF2F857FD97F84C" box="[549,635,1940,1966]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,761,785]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,179,735]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[164,1423,179,736]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhopalopsole singiplatta, sp. nov. A. male head and pronotum, dorsal view; B. female head and pronotum, dorsal view; C. female abdominal terminalia, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524476" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524476/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Legs brown. Wings hyaline and veins light brown. Subgenital plate on sternum 8 produced into a broadly triangular extension with a middle knotch, hind margin strongly sclerotized as well as hind part of central area (
<figureCitation id="669A2A513C08EF06FDD0F81FFDB3F814" box="[519,607,2012,2038]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,761,785]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,179,735]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[164,1423,179,736]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhopalopsole singiplatta, sp. nov. A. male head and pronotum, dorsal view; B. female head and pronotum, dorsal view; C. female abdominal terminalia, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524476" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524476/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="271">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Transverse bar in sternum 9 evenly sclerotized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
