<subSubSection id="B6BB655F3C0BEF05FF10F986FE26F961" pageId="2" pageNumber="272" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="FE1E36D43C0BEF05FF10F986FE26F961" blockId="2.[151,1436,1533,2027]" pageId="2" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0BEF05FF10F986FEA2F9BD" bold="true" box="[199,334,1605,1631]" pageId="2" pageNumber="272">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name refers to lateral bars blending with the central plate of tergum 10 of the adult male to form a single plate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B6BB655F3C0BEF04FF10F94EFB9BFB01" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="273" pageId="2" pageNumber="272" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="FE1E36D43C0BEF05FF10F94EFD0FF841" blockId="2.[151,1436,1533,2027]" pageId="2" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0BEF05FF10F94EFE0EF945" bold="true" box="[199,482,1677,1703]" pageId="2" pageNumber="272">Diagnosis and remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="39A14D573C0BEF05FE3EF94EFCEFF945" authority="Yang &amp; Du &amp; Zhu, 2022" authorityName="Yang &amp; Du &amp; Zhu" authorityYear="2022" box="[489,771,1677,1703]" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Rhopalopsole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singiplatta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0BEF05FE3EF94EFCEFF945" box="[489,771,1677,1703]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="272">Rhopalopsole singiplatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0BEF05FCDDF94EFC88F945" bold="true" box="[778,868,1677,1703]" pageId="2" pageNumber="272">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D7E657BD3C0BEF05FCDDF94EFC88F945" box="[778,868,1677,1703]" pageId="2" pageNumber="272" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is a member of the 
<taxonomicName id="39A14D573C0BEF05FB93F94DFF23F929" authority="Sivec &amp; Harper, 2008" authorityName="Sivec &amp; Harper" authorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Rhopalopsole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vietnamica">
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0BEF05FB93F94DFB33F945" box="[1092,1247,1678,1703]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="272">R. vietnamica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="9A304B253C0BEF05FB31F94EFF23F929" author="Sivec, I. &amp; Harper, P. P. &amp; Shimizu, T." pageId="2" pageNumber="272" pagination="1 - 122" refId="ref6152" refString="Sivec, I., Harper, P. P. &amp; Shimizu, T. (2008) Contribution to the study of the Oriental genus Rhopalopsole (Plecoptera: Leuctridae). Scopolia, 64, 1 - 122." type="journal article" year="2008">Sivec &amp; Harper, 2008</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
west group as proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="9A304B253C0BEF05FDD5F972FD3DF929" author="Sivec, I. &amp; Harper, P. P. &amp; Shimizu, T." box="[514,721,1713,1739]" pageId="2" pageNumber="272" pagination="1 - 122" refId="ref6152" refString="Sivec, I., Harper, P. P. &amp; Shimizu, T. (2008) Contribution to the study of the Oriental genus Rhopalopsole (Plecoptera: Leuctridae). Scopolia, 64, 1 - 122." type="journal article" year="2008">
Sivec 
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0BEF05FD90F971FD9BF929" box="[583,631,1713,1739]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="272">et al</emphasis>
. (2008)
</bibRefCitation>
, with tergum 10 of the adult male possessing a central plate with lateral bars strongly sclerotized, lateral projections typically ending in a forked process, epiproct simple and thick, and subanal lobes typical of this group. At present, this new species is the largest species of 
<taxonomicName id="39A14D573C0BEF05FB42F93AFAC3F8F1" authorityName="Klapalek" authorityYear="1912" box="[1173,1327,1785,1811]" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Rhopalopsole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0BEF05FB42F93AFAC3F8F1" box="[1173,1327,1785,1811]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="272">Rhopalopsole</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="86B676443C0BEF05FA85F93AFA74F8F1" box="[1362,1432,1785,1811]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="272">China</collectingCountry>
, approximately 2X the average length. The male of the new species appears most closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="39A14D573C0BEF05FB28F8DDFEDAF8B9" authority="Li &amp; Yang, 2010" authorityName="Li &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Rhopalopsole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hainana">
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0BEF05FB28F8DDFA97F8D5" box="[1279,1403,1821,1847]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="272">R. hainana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="9A304B253C0BEF05FA54F8DEFEDAF8B9" author="Li, W. H. &amp; Yang, D." pageId="2" pageNumber="272" pagination="59 - 64" refId="ref5293" refString="Li, W. H. &amp; Yang, D. (2010) Two new species of Rhopalopsole vietnamica group (Plecoptera: Leuctridae: Rhopalopsole) from China. Zootaxa, 2614 (1), 59 - 64. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2614.1.6" type="journal article" year="2010">Li &amp; Yang, 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by sharing a similar epiproct. but can be separated from the latter by lateral projections on tergum 10 with the length of upper spine being equal to the lower one in lateral view, the cercus of the new species lacks a spine while that of 
<taxonomicName id="39A14D573C0BEF05FEB9F849FE05F841" authorityName="Li &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2010" box="[366,489,1929,1955]" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Rhopalopsole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hainana">
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0BEF05FEB9F849FE05F841" box="[366,489,1929,1955]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="272">R. hainana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a subapical spine.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FE1E36D43C0BEF04FF10F86EFD68FE87" blockId="2.[151,1436,1533,2027]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,151,357]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="273" pageId="2" pageNumber="272">
The new species is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="39A14D573C0BEF05FD99F86DFD0EF825" authorityName="Li, Muranyi &amp; Gamboa" authorityYear="2017" box="[590,738,1965,1991]" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Rhopalopsole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cestroidea">
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0BEF05FD99F86DFD0EF825" box="[590,738,1965,1991]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="272">R. cestroidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They share a similar lateral projection of tergum 10 with the length of upper spine being subequal to lower one in lateral view and the cercus of both species lacks a spine. But the new species can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="39A14D573C0AEF04FD87FF54FD08FF53" authorityName="Li, Muranyi &amp; Gamboa" authorityYear="2017" box="[592,740,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Rhopalopsole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cestroidea">
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0AEF04FD87FF54FD08FF53" box="[592,740,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">R. cestroidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by tergum 10 bearing a central plate with macrotrichia lateral bars that are heavily sclerotized. 
<taxonomicName id="39A14D573C0AEF04FDDCFF78FCCDFF37" authorityName="Li, Muranyi &amp; Gamboa" authorityYear="2017" box="[523,801,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Rhopalopsole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cestroidea">
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0AEF04FDDCFF78FCCDFF37" box="[523,801,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">Rhopalopsole cestroidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an epiproct that is much wider than long and nearly as wide as the central plate, the central plate sclerotized, with posterior half darker with a quadrate medial elevation but without lateral bars. The shape of subgenital plate of the female of the new species is a trapezoid, and there are two sclerotized spots on the upper edge (
<figureCitation id="669A2A513C0AEF04FD8DFEE4FD43FEA3" box="[602,687,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,761,785]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,179,735]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[164,1423,179,736]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhopalopsole singiplatta, sp. nov. A. male head and pronotum, dorsal view; B. female head and pronotum, dorsal view; C. female abdominal terminalia, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524476" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524476/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
), while that of 
<taxonomicName id="39A14D573C0AEF04FC81FEE4FC05FEA3" authorityName="Li, Muranyi &amp; Gamboa" authorityYear="2017" box="[854,1001,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Rhopalopsole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cestroidea">
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0AEF04FC81FEE4FC05FEA3" box="[854,1001,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">R. cestroidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is more like a square and without spots on the upper edge (fig. 
<quantity id="39599B313C0AEF04FE4BFE88FE39FE87" box="[412,469,331,357]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.318" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" unit="in" value="17.0">17 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="9A304B253C0AEF04FE0BFE88FD94FE87" author="Li, W. H. &amp; Muranyi, D. &amp; Gamboa, M. &amp; Yang, D. &amp; Watanabe, K." box="[476,632,331,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" pagination="165 - 176" refId="ref5450" refString="Li, W. H., Muranyi, D., Gamboa, M., Yang, D. &amp; Watanabe, K. (2017) New species and records of Leuctridae (Plecoptera) from Guangxi, China, on the basis of morphological and molecular data, with emphasis on Rhopalopsole. Zootaxa, 4243 (1), 165 - 176. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4243.1.8" type="journal article" year="2017">
Li 
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0AEF04FE2BFE88FDC1FE87" box="[508,557,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="AADE665C3C0AEF04FF40FC0DFD9BFBE9" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524481" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6524481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524481/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" startId="3.[151,250,974,998]" targetBox="[196,1389,387,947]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="FE1E36D43C0AEF04FF40FC0DFD9BFBE9" blockId="3.[151,1437,974,1035]" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0AEF04FF40FC0DFEFAFC04" bold="true" box="[151,278,974,998]" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="39A14D573C0AEF04FEF7FC0CFDCCFC05" authority="Yang &amp; Du &amp; Zhu, 2022" authorityName="Yang &amp; Du &amp; Zhu" authorityYear="2022" box="[288,544,975,999]" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Rhopalopsole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singiplatta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0AEF04FEF7FC0CFDCCFC05" box="[288,544,975,999]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">Rhopalopsole singiplatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0AEF04FDE6FC0CFD68FC05" bold="true" box="[561,644,975,999]" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D7E657BD3C0AEF04FDE6FC0CFD68FC05" box="[561,644,975,999]" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
A: male abdominal terminalia, dorsal view; B: male abdominal terminalia, ventral view; C: lateral processes of tergum 10.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="FE1E36D43C0AEF04FF10FBFAFB9BFB01" blockId="3.[151,1436,1081,1251]" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0AEF04FF10FBFAFE40FBB1" bold="true" box="[199,428,1081,1107]" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">Molecular analysis.</emphasis>
The Maximum Likelihood tree supported the morphological distinction of 
<taxonomicName id="39A14D573C0AEF04FB36FBF9FA9AFBB1" authority="Yang &amp; Du &amp; Zhu, 2022" authorityName="Yang &amp; Du &amp; Zhu" authorityYear="2022" box="[1249,1398,1081,1107]" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Rhopalopsole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singiplatta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0AEF04FB36FBF9FA9AFBB1" box="[1249,1398,1081,1107]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">R. singiplatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0AEF04FAACFBFAFF24FB95" bold="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D7E657BD3C0AEF04FAACFBFAFF24FB95" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and the separation from the five other species of 
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0AEF04FD3DFB9EFC68FB95" box="[746,900,1117,1143]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">Rholapopsole</emphasis>
with 100% nodal support. (
<figureCitation id="669A2A513C0AEF04FB6FFB9EFB11FB95" box="[1208,1277,1117,1143]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1686,1710]" captionTargetBox="[360,1227,1282,1658]" captionTargetId="figure-246@3.[352,1235,1275,1662]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 4. Phylogenetic relationships among 9 species of Leuctridae based on a Maximum Likelihood tree analysis. Numbers at the nodes represent bootstrap values as percentages. Only nodal support values&gt;70% are depicted on the tree. Genus names are marked to the right of each species. M = male, F = female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524483" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524483/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Interspecific divergence values for 
<taxonomicName id="39A14D573C0AEF04FE5AFB41FDC8FB79" authority="Yang &amp; Du &amp; Zhu, 2022" authorityName="Yang &amp; Du &amp; Zhu" authorityYear="2022" box="[397,548,1153,1179]" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Rhopalopsole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singiplatta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0AEF04FE5AFB41FDC8FB79" box="[397,548,1153,1179]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">R. singiplatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0AEF04FDFDFB42FD6FFB79" bold="true" box="[554,643,1153,1179]" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D7E657BD3C0AEF04FDFDFB42FD6FFB79" box="[554,643,1153,1179]" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
ranged from 14.5–25.0% of genetic divergence in comparison with the other species whereas intraspecific between an associated male-female pair was only 1.1%. Combined, this is good evidence for the validity of 
<taxonomicName id="39A14D573C0AEF04FE1AFB09FD89FB01" authority="Yang &amp; Du &amp; Zhu, 2022" authorityName="Yang &amp; Du &amp; Zhu" authorityYear="2022" box="[461,613,1225,1251]" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Rhopalopsole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singiplatta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0AEF04FE1AFB09FD89FB01" box="[461,613,1225,1251]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">R. singiplatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0AEF04FDBCFB0AFD29FB01" bold="true" box="[619,709,1225,1251]" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D7E657BD3C0AEF04FDBCFB0AFD29FB01" box="[619,709,1225,1251]" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="9A304B253C0AEF04FD04FB0AFC4EFB01" author="Hebert, P. D. &amp; Ratnasingham, S. &amp; de Waard, J. R." box="[723,930,1225,1251]" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" pagination="96 - 99" refId="ref4973" refString="Hebert, P. D., Ratnasingham, S. &amp; de Waard, J. R. (2003) Barcoding animal life: cytochrome c oxidase subunit 1 divergences among closely related species. Proceedings of the Royal Society of London, Series B (Biological Sciences), 270 (Supplement 1), 96 - 99. https: // doi. org / 10.1098 / rsbl. 2003.0025" type="journal article" year="2003">
Hebert 
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0AEF04FCFFFB09FCB6FB01" box="[808,858,1225,1251]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="9A304B253C0AEF04FC7AFB0AFB87FB01" author="Zhou, X. &amp; Adamowicz, S. J. &amp; Jacobus, L. M. &amp; DeWalt, R. E. &amp; Hebert, P. D." box="[941,1131,1225,1251]" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" pagination="30" refId="ref6893" refString="Zhou, X., Adamowicz, S. J., Jacobus, L. M., DeWalt, R. E. &amp; Hebert, P. D. (2009) Towards a comprehensive barcode library for Arctic life-Ephemeroptera, Plecoptera, and Trichoptera of Churchill, Manitoba, Canada. Frontiers in Zoology, 6 (1), 30. https: // doi. org / 10.1186 / 1742 - 9994 - 6 - 30" type="journal article" year="2009">
Zhou 
<emphasis id="CCD5EAC63C0AEF04FC38FB09FBCDFB01" box="[1007,1057,1225,1251]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">et al</emphasis>
. 2009
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
